==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*xluþaz'', from Indo-European ''*klutos-'', past participle of ''*kleu-'' ‘hear’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[lud|lūd]], Old Saxon [[hlud#Old Saxon|hlūd]] (Dutch [[luid]]), Old High German [[hlut|hlūt]], ''[[lūt]]'' (German ''[[laut]]'').  The IE past participle is also the source of Greek [[κλυτός]] ‘renowned’, Latin [[inclutus]], Welsh [[clod]] ‘praise’.

